\begin{abstract}
For an arbitrary Euclidean building   we define a certain
combing, which satisfies the ``fellow traveller property''
and admits a recursive definition.
 Using this combing we prove that any group acting freely, cocompactly
and by order preserving automorphisms
on a  Euclidean building of one of the types $A_n,B_n,C_n$ 
admits a  biautomatic structure.
\end{abstract}

